    "name": "LMS B2B - GraphQL API (Full Suite)",
    "_postman_id": "b7f0a5f0-1a2b-4c3d-8e5f-000000000002",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection mirroring the Java/TestNG suite.\n\nStructure — one folder per module, split into **Positive** and **Negative** sub-folders:\n- Auth (Login / Me / negative scenarios)\n- System (Ping)\n- Company\n- Angkatan (cohort)\n- Employee\n- Division (class)\n- Program (program studi)\n- Announcement\n- Bootcamp (fast-track class)\n- Media Library\n\nHow to use:\n1. Import this JSON via Postman → File → Import.\n2. Kredensial sudah tersimpan di collection variables (from config.properties).\n3. Run **Auth → Positive → Login** first — the test-script menyimpan cookie `sid_b2b` sebagai collection variable, otomatis dipakai request lain.\n4. Untuk CRUD flow (Angkatan/Employee/Division/Program/Announcement/Bootcamp) jalankan urutan Create → GetById → Update → Delete karena tiap request menyimpan/mengambil id dari collection variable.\n5. Gunakan Collection Runner untuk menjalankan semua folder sekaligus.\n\nGlobal test scripts memvalidasi HTTP 200 dan mengecek `errors` di response.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "auth": {
    "type": "basic",
    "basic": [
      { "key": "username", "value": "{{usernameGraphQL}}", "type": "string" },
      { "key": "password", "value": "{{passwordGraphQL}}", "type": "string" }
    ]
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "test",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Global test-script: applied to every request in the collection.",
          "pm.test('Status code is 200', function () { pm.response.to.have.status(200); });",
          "// A 'positive' request expects no `errors`; the negative folders override this",
          "// script with request-level scripts that assert the presence of `errors`.",
          "if (!pm.info.requestName.startsWith('[NEG]')) {",
          "    pm.test('Response has no GraphQL errors', function () {",
          "        const json = pm.response.json();",
          "        pm.expect(json.errors, 'errors field').to.be.oneOf([undefined, null]);",
          "    });",
          "}"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
